Association of California School Administrators
April 30 at 11:01 AM ·

We're so excited to bring you a new edition of ACSA News, a broadcast focusing on all of the POSITIVE stories in California education. Get ready to be inspired by the incredible creativity from students and educators around the state. Plus, we visit with Mary McNeil from Needles Unified School District to discuss some of the challenges she's facing as superintendent in a rural community. Featuring apperances from students and educators in these great school districts: Roseville City School District Capistrano Unified School District Roseville Joint Union High School District Needles Unified School District Palm Springs Unified School District

Do you want to share a positive story with us? Just email goodnews@acsa.org! #ACSAGoodNews #ACSAInspirationThursday

post_text:
Monterey County Health Officer Issues Mandatory Face Covering Order
Post Date:04/28/2020

To help stop the spread of COVID-19, the Monterey County Health Officer is requiring residents to wear a face covering when going out into the public to perform essential activities, effective 12:01 a.m. on Thursday, April 30, 2020. Combined with sheltering in place, social distancing, and frequent hand hygiene, facial coverings are shown to help slow transmission of COVID-19.

The adult school will have homemade masks available to staff, one per staff member, until they are gone, at the high school between 11:00 and 12:30 today and tomorrow.

In case you can't get to the high school, our own, Toula Hubbard and her daughter, created this video that will demonstrate how you can make a mask from a shirt you may already have in your closet!
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=daF55GCoMVQ&feature=youtu.be

post_text:
Good morning teachers,
We hope you and your students are having and positive and productive week.

If you haven't already heard about this, Google for Education recently announced the launch of their distance learning support hub called Teach From Home: https://teachfromhome.google/intl/en/

In a nutshell, Teach From Home is comprised of tools, video tutorials, tips, and professional learning forums (#TeachFromHome) - all geared towards supporting your efforts during these challenging times.

We've linked Teach From Home to our own Distance Learning Support Site.

Be well and stay safe,
